    evidenceSummary: "Creatine monohydrate is the most studied sports supplement, with ~30 years of safety data and robust efficacy for strength + lean mass. ISSN 2017 position stand (Kreider et al.): supports 5g/day for cellular saturation, no loading phase needed. Safety established up to 5 years (Kreider 2003) in healthy adults. Forbes 2021 systematic review: creatine + resistance training in older adults = ~1.4 kg more lean mass + 5-10% more strength than RT alone. Cognitive: Roschel 2021 review found small but consistent improvements in working memory and intelligence test performance in older adults (less benefit in young healthy). Mechanism: increases phosphocreatine pool -> faster ATP regeneration -> more high-quality reps; in brain, may buffer ATP under stress (sleep deprivation, cognitive load). Practical: 5g monohydrate daily, any time, with or without food. Skip the loading phase. Plateau effect ~3-4 weeks. Expect 1-2 kg water-weight gain in muscle (intracellular water — that's the mechanism). CKD patients: discuss with nephrologist; healthy kidney function is not a contraindication.",
