    verdict: "If you have hypertension, this is one of the highest-value interventions you can make. The direct longevity benefit beyond BP control is modest but real. Combined with statins, ACEi/ARBs are the workhorses of preventive cardiology.",
    todo: ["If your BP is consistently above 130/80, get a workup. Don't just live with high BP.", "First-line options: ramipril (5–10 mg), lisinopril (10–40 mg), telmisartan (40–80 mg). All once daily.", "If you get a dry persistent cough on ACE inhibitor (~10% of people), switch to an ARB (sartan ending). Same benefits, no cough.", "Take it the same time every day. Bedtime dosing has slight evidence for cardiovascular benefit (the 'Hygia' study).", "Get blood work at 2–4 weeks after starting and after dose changes: potassium and creatinine.", "Stop immediately if you become pregnant or are trying to conceive — these are teratogenic.", "Don't combine ACE inhibitor + ARB. Pick one."],
