    todo: ["Use 30–50 ml/day (~2–3 tablespoons) as your default cooking and dressing fat.", "Buy high-polyphenol EVOO. Look for: harvest date within 12 months, dark glass or tin (NOT clear plastic), 'extra virgin' (not just 'virgin' or 'olive oil'), single-origin if possible.", "Better signals of quality: pungent peppery sting at the back of the throat, bitter green flavor. That's polyphenols. Smooth/buttery EVOO has fewer of them.", "Store in a dark cupboard, away from heat. Cap tight. Use within 12 months of opening.", "Cooking: yes, you can cook with EVOO — its smoke point is high enough for most home use. Don't deep fry.", "Drizzle raw on salads, vegetables, soups, eggs, fish, bread. The polyphenols are heat-degraded, so raw use preserves the most.", "Brands worth knowing: Brightland (US), Kosterina, Apollo, or local producers if you live in a Mediterranean region."],
    forYou: "Almost everyone. Among the highest evidence-graded foods on the planet.",
