    mechanism: "Your brain has a master clock that needs a daily light signal to stay synchronized — without it, sleep timing, hormone release, and even gene expression in every cell drift out of phase. Morning bright light (especially direct sunlight, 10,000+ lux) is by far the strongest 'reset' signal. The window matters: light in the first hour after waking sets that day's rhythm and the timing of melatonin release 14–16 hours later. Skin sun exposure is a separate issue — moderate, sub-burning exposure has all-cause mortality benefits in cohort studies; aggressive avoidance loses some of that.",
