    plain: "Collagen peptides have real evidence for skin elasticity, joint pain reduction, and tendon repair — but as a longevity headline, it's tertiary. Don't take it instead of total dietary protein; take it on top of, or as part of, hitting your daily protein target.",
    mechanism: "Collagen is the structural protein in your skin, joints, tendons, and bones. When you eat hydrolyzed collagen, you get specific amino acids (glycine, proline, hydroxyproline) and small bioactive peptide fragments that signal your skin and joint cells to make more new collagen. The mechanism is real — but at the end of the day, your body still mostly cares that you're getting enough total protein. Collagen is a partial protein source, not a complete one.",
