    plain: "CoQ10 is genuinely useful in two specific situations: heart failure and statin-induced muscle aches. For healthy adults seeking general longevity, the evidence is thin. If your doctor has you on a statin and you have muscle aches, try this before switching drugs. Otherwise, low priority.",
    mechanism: "Inside your mitochondria — the cellular power plants — there's an electron-shuttle molecule called CoQ10 that's essential for making energy. Your body makes it, but production drops with age. Statins (cholesterol drugs) also reduce CoQ10 because they share part of the same biosynthesis pathway. In people with heart failure or statin-related muscle aches, supplementing CoQ10 sometimes makes a real, noticeable difference. In healthy adults, the effect is much harder to detect.",
