    mechanism: "Taurine is an amino acid your body uses for several maintenance jobs: making bile acids that help digest fat, calming overactive cells, supporting your mitochondria, and acting as an antioxidant. Your levels naturally drop dramatically as you age — by 80 you have roughly 20% of what you had at 18. The theory is that restoring taurine to youthful levels helps the systems that depend on it.",
