    todo: ["Pick an 8–10 hour eating window and keep it consistent. Common choice: 11am–7pm or 10am–6pm.", "If possible, skip dinner instead of breakfast — early eating is metabolically slightly better.", "Drink water, plain tea, or black coffee outside the window. Anything with calories breaks the fast.", "Don't compress your normal calories into a binge. Aim for the same total food, different timing.", "Keep protein intake high (1.6 g/kg bodyweight). Tighter windows risk muscle loss without enough protein.", "Don't combine with extreme calorie restriction unless you know what you're doing.", "If you have an eating disorder history, skip this entirely. The structure can become disordered fast."],
