    todo: ["If you take NMN or NR: pair with 500–1000 mg TMG/day. Take same time as the NAD+ precursor.", "If you don't take NMN/NR: probably skip TMG unless your homocysteine is elevated.", "Powder form is cheap and tasteless; capsules are convenient.", "Beets and spinach are natural sources — useful background but not enough to replace a deliberate methyl-donor supplement when stacking NAD+ precursors.", "Watch your LDL cholesterol — TMG at high doses (>3 g/day) has been shown to raise LDL slightly.", "If you have high LDL, use lower doses (500 mg) or skip.", "Mild fishy body odor is a rare side effect; back off if it happens."],
