    verdict: "Most credible 'longevity supplement' with a real mechanism. Hit-and-run dosing is biologically reasonable. Watch for the Mayo human trial readouts. Until then: low cost, low risk, plausible upside.",
    todo: ["Hit-and-run protocol: 1000–1500 mg/day for 2 consecutive days, once per month. Not daily.", "Take with fat (olive oil, full-fat yogurt, fatty meal) — bioavailability is poor without it.", "Look for 'novusetin' or liposomal fisetin formulations — better absorbed than plain capsules.", "Standard caps (100–500 mg/day daily) are the alternative if you don't want pulse dosing — weaker theoretical case but sometimes used.", "Stop and reassess if you're on anticoagulants — theoretical interaction.", "Watch the Mayo Clinic Phase 2 trial readouts (search 'fisetin senolytic clinical trial' periodically).", "Don't combine with active cancer treatment without oncologist sign-off."],
